  "title": "Associate CyberSecurity Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Ensure timely and clear communication with all stakeholders.</li><li>Liaise with customers and vendors for issue resolution.</li><li>Review business workflows or system functionalities and recommend improvements.</li><li>Provide 24/7 operational support to ensure system availability.</li><li>Troubleshoot cybersecurity issues, including fault isolation.</li><li>Execute scheduled preventive maintenance for optimal system performance.</li><li>Manage service requests and incidents for timely resolution.</li><li>Collaborate with service providers/vendors to meet SLAs.</li><li>Support critical events on a rotational basis as needed.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in IT, Computer Science, Engineering, or equivalent.</li><li>Professional certifications in cybersecurity solutions are a plus.</li><li>Min 2 years of relevant experience preferred; fresh graduates are welcome to apply.</li><li>Experience in operations support.</li><li>Strong knowledge of <strong>Windows</strong> and/or <strong>Linux </strong>operating systems.</li><li>Hands-on experience with cybersecurity tools such as <strong>McAfee, Cisco, Microsoft, Thales.</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Work Location:</strong> Tampines<br /></p><p>(EA Reg No: 20C0312)<br />Please email a copy of your detailed resume to <strong>qianyu@talentsis.com.sg</strong> for immediate processing.<br />Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>",
